---
import Shell from '../layouts/Shell.astro';
---

<Shell title="Disclaimer" branch="home">
  <section class="px-5 pt-10 pb-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">Disclaimer</h1>

    <div class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Good Medicine provides general educational information about financial topics
        relevant to First Nations communities in Canada. It is designed to help you
        understand your options, not to tell you what to do.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">This is not legal advice, tax advice, or financial advice.</strong>
        Nothing in this app should be taken as a substitute for professional guidance
        tailored to your specific situation.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary pt-4">Section 87 and tax information</h2>
      <p>
        The Section 87 guidance in this app is based on general principles and the
        connecting factors test as understood at the time of writing. Individual
        situations vary significantly. If your situation involves mixed factors or
        grey areas, consult a qualified tax professional with experience in
        Indigenous tax matters.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary pt-4">Benefit amounts and tax rates</h2>
      <p>
        Dollar amounts, tax rates, and benefit thresholds referenced in this app
        are approximate and based on publicly available information as of the date
        noted below. These figures can change with government budgets and policy
        updates. Always confirm current amounts with the relevant program or agency.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary pt-4">NIHB coverage</h2>
      <p>
        Non-Insured Health Benefits coverage details may vary by region and
        individual circumstance. Confirm your specific coverage by contacting
        NIHB directly or speaking with your health care provider.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary pt-4">Your privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This app does not collect, store, or transmit personal data. All information
        you enter — check-ins, budgets, savings goals, tool results — stays on your
        device in your browser's local storage. There are no accounts, no servers
        receiving your data, and no tracking of any kind.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary pt-4">Content review</h2>
      <p>
        Content was last reviewed March 2026.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary pt-4">Professional advice</h2>
      <p>
        For advice specific to your situation, consult a qualified accountant,
        lawyer, or financial advisor — ideally one with experience in Indigenous
        tax and financial matters. Your Band office may be able to recommend
        professionals familiar with your community's circumstances.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary pt-4">Crisis resources</h2>
      <p>
        Crisis resources are provided in this app for informational purposes.
        If you are in immediate danger, call 911. If you are experiencing a
        mental health crisis, contact the First Nations and Inuit Hope for
        Wellness Help Line at 1-855-242-3310 (available 24/7).
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Shell>
